        <h2><a href="#TOCintroduction" name="introduction">Introduction</a></h2>

        <p> JScreenRecorder is a free and opensource pure java based screen
            recording software licensed under LGPL.<br />
        </p>

        <p>The following features are available so far :</p>

        <ul>

            <li>Free software available under the Lesser GNU Public License</li>
            <li>Fullscreen and selective screen area recording<br />
            </li>
            <li>Custom cursors<br />
            </li>
            <li>Chooses from a set of 128 different cursors<br />
            </li>
            <li>Cursor highlighter<br />
            </li>
            <li>Highlighter color and alpha(transparency) settings<br />
            </li>
            <li>Support for watermarking<br />
            </li>
            <li>Create custom textual watermark <br />
            </li>
            <li>Watermark alpha(transparency) settings<br />
            </li>
            <li>WYSIWYG (What You See Is What You Get) type of Watermark location
                selector</li>
            <li>Frame rate setting<br />
            </li>
            <li>Runs on all major Java supported platforms</li>
            <li>Uses JMF (Java Media Framework), TransPanel and JTextChooser components<br />
            </li>

            <li>Encodes video in AVI format<br />
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2><a href="#TOCdownloading" name="downloading">Downloading</a></h2>

        <p> JScreenRecorder can be found at the <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/jscreenrecorder/">JScreenRecorder's
                SourceForge Page</a>.
        </p>

